      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3/12/85 ¶  ¶  ¶ Would you oblige me, dear Mr Carruthers, by ascertaining, whether in your collections from Forster’s Herbarium ¶ Most of the plant specimens collected by Johann Reinhold Forster and hi...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.12.03a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Carruthers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Natural History Museum, London, Museum Archives, DF404/5, folder 71,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mueller, Sir FJH von.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3/12/85<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you oblige me, dear Mr Carruthers, by ascertaining, whether in your collections from Forster’s Herbarium<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Most of the plant specimens collected by Johann Reinhold Forster and his son George during James Cook's second voyage of exploration (1772-4)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>had gone<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to the British Museum, where Carruthers was based.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>specimens of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Myoporum pubescens<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or M. crassifolium exist. The former is left unnoticed for N. Zeal. by Sir J. Hooker; perhaps it is a downy form of M. laetum; the other may be M. insulare,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">if Botanices Insula means Botany Bay</hi>
               </seg>, (is this so?) in which case the specific name may also have originated with Solander.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>G. Forster (1786a), p. 44, listed four species of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Myoporum</seg>, namely<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">M. laetum</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">M. pubescens</seg>, both said to be from NZ,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">M. crassifolium</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from 'Botanices insula', and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">M. tenuifolium</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from New Caledonia. J. Hooker (1853-5), vol. 1, pp. 204-5, gives<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">M. laetum</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as the only<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Myoporum</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from NZ and remarks: '<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Myoporum pubescens</seg>, Forst. Prodr., is quite unknown to me, and probably belongs to some other genus'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Botanices Insula' is a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>small islet near New Caledonia.<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">G.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Forster (1777), vol. 2, p. 439, entry for 30 September 1774:</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.6666in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">Captain Cook gave this little islet the name of Botany Island, because it contained in so small a space a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">flora</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of nearly thirty species, among which we saw several new ones. Its situation is nearly 22°<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>28'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">S. and 167° 16' E.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If these two dubious plants are available in your collection would you oblige with sending fragments to me.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No specimens of these species are preserved in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Forster Collection in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne herbarium.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My monograph[y] of Myoporinae is almost completed, so far as the 80 Quarto-plates are concerned.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The plates were published in B86.08.05. No text volume was ever published.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I trust, you will take a favorable view as regards my propositions concerning Mr Forbes Papuan plants.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was seeking to have a role in describing the plants collected<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in an expedition<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>funded by British bodies<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by Henry Forbes,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who had arrived in Port Morseby<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in September and had offered support for M's work on Papuan plants.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>H. Forbes to M, 19 September 1885 (in this edition as 85-09-19c) and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to W. Carruthers, 21 October 1885<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 85-10-21a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myoporum crassifolium</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myoporum insulare</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myoporum laetum</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myoporum pubescens</p>
         </div>
      </body>
